<subSubSection pageId="54" pageNumber="55" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="54.[146,770,1190,1474]" box="[146,312,1190,1210]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
<figureCitation box="[146,312,1190,1210]" captionStart="Plate 19" captionStartId="54.[146,187,1014,1031]" captionTargetBox="[165,1442,147,979]" captionTargetPageId="54" captionText="Plate 19. Emargininae. Fig. 249, Thoreauella sp., USNMENT01022106. Fig. 250, Thoreauella sp., USNMENT01525887." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4552268" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4552268/files/figure.png" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Figs. 249 and 250</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[146,770,1190,1474]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
This unusual group of diminutive wasps has been variously classified, often as eucoilines. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronquist, F." box="[406,564,1248,1268]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="139 - 164" refId="ref27726" refString="Ronquist, F. 1999. Phylogeny, classification and evolution of the Cynipoidea. Zool. Scr. 28: 139 - 164." type="journal article" year="1999">Ronquist (1999)</bibRefCitation>
clarified the circumscription of the group and recognized them as their own subfamily (reviewed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pujade-Villar, J." box="[269,443,1307,1327]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="18 - 65" refId="ref26799" refString="Pujade-Villar, J. 2019. Reclasificacion de los grandes taxa de Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera) desde Weld (1952) hasta 2017: la historia de una lucha evolutiva entre el parasitoidismo y la fitofagia. Folia Entomol. Mex. 5: 18 - 65." type="journal article" year="2019">Pujade-Villar 2019</bibRefCitation>
). While typically rare in most parts of the world, they are a dominant figitid group in 
<collectingCountry box="[610,723,1336,1356]" name="Madagascar" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="van Noort, S. &amp; M. L. Buffington &amp; M. Forshage" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref26145" refString="van Noort, S., M. L. Buffington, and M. Forshage. 2015. Afrotropical Cynipoidea. Zookeys. 493: 1 - 176. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 493.6353." type="journal article" year="2015">van Noort et al. 2015</bibRefCitation>
). Several genera have been described, but all have been synonymized under 
<taxonomicName authority="Girault" authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1930" box="[401,593,1395,1415]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Thoreauella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[401,511,1395,1415]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thoreauella</emphasis>
Girault
</taxonomicName>
; considering that, nothing less than a world-wide revision would be able to find phylogenetically meaningful groups.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[146,770,1507,1556]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Biology. Host unknown, but adults have been collected from formicid refuse piles (
<bibRefCitation author="Weld, L. H." box="[345,457,1536,1556]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="195 - 196" refId="ref28960" refString="Weld, L. H. 1960 b. A new genus in Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera). Proc. Entomol. Soc. Wash. 62: 195 - 196." type="journal article" year="1960">Weld 1960b</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[146,770,1587,1636]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Distribution. Pantropical and transgressing into Eastern Palearctic, but rarely collected outside 
<collectingCountry box="[401,514,1616,1636]" name="Madagascar" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[146,771,1667,1775]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">
Relevant literature. 
<bibRefCitation author="Ronquist, F." box="[346,507,1667,1687]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="139 - 164" refId="ref27726" refString="Ronquist, F. 1999. Phylogeny, classification and evolution of the Cynipoidea. Zool. Scr. 28: 139 - 164." type="journal article" year="1999">Ronquist (1999)</bibRefCitation>
circumscribed the group; 
<bibRefCitation author="Weld, L. H." box="[146,274,1696,1716]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="195 - 196" refId="ref28960" refString="Weld, L. H. 1960 b. A new genus in Cynipoidea (Hymenoptera). Proc. Entomol. Soc. Wash. 62: 195 - 196." type="journal article" year="1960">Weld (1960b)</bibRefCitation>
suggested species are ant associates. 
<bibRefCitation author="van Noort, S. &amp; M. L. Buffington &amp; M. Forshage" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" pagination="1 - 176" refId="ref26145" refString="van Noort, S., M. L. Buffington, and M. Forshage. 2015. Afrotropical Cynipoidea. Zookeys. 493: 1 - 176. doi: 10.3897 / zookeys. 493.6353." type="journal article" year="2015">Van Noort et al. (2015)</bibRefCitation>
reviewed the Afrotropical species and moved all species into 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Girault" authorityYear="1930" box="[146,256,1755,1775]" class="Insecta" family="Figitidae" genus="Thoreauella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="54" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[146,256,1755,1775]" italics="true" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Thoreauella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="54.[146,276,1808,1828]" box="[146,276,1808,1828]" pageId="54" pageNumber="55">Classification.</paragraph>
